        <div id="story-meta" class="story-meta ">
                            <div class="supported-by hidden nocontent robots-nocontent">
                    <span class="ad-label">Supported by</span>
                    <div id="supported-by-ad" class="supported-by-ad ad"></div>
                </div>
                                        <h3 class="kicker">
                                            <span class="kicker-label"><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/section/opinion/campaign-stops">The Opinion Pages</a></span>                                                    <span class="pipe">|</span><span class="subsection-kicker-label">
                                                            <a href="http://www.nytimes.com/section/opinion/campaign-stops">Campaign Stops</a></span>
                                                                                        </h3>
                        			<h1 itemprop="headline" id="headline" class="headline">Donald Trump’s Real Message on Race</h1>
	                                                <div id="story-meta-footer" class="story-meta-footer">
                <div class="extended-byline">
    <div class="thumb">
        <a href="http://www.nytimes.com/by/andrew-rosenthal">            <img src="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2016/06/07/opinion/andy-rosenthal/andy-rosenthal-thumbLarge-v2.jpg" title="Andrew Rosenthal" />
        </a>    </div>
    <div class="byline-meta">
                <p class="byline-column has-single-author">
                            <a class="byline-column-link" href="http://www.nytimes.com/column/andrew-rosenthal">Andrew Rosenthal</a>
                        <time class="dateline" datetime="2016-09-23T02:36:32-04:00" itemprop="dateModified" content="2016-09-23T02:36:32-04:00">SEPT. 22, 2016</time>
        </p>
    </div><!-- close byline-meta -->
</div><!-- close extended-byline -->
                                                
                                    <div class="story-meta-footer-sharetools">
                        <div id="sharetools-story-meta-footer" aria-label="tools" role="group" class="sharetools theme-classic  sharetools-story-meta-footer  "
data-shares="facebook,twitter,email,show-all,save"
data-url="http://www.nytimes.com/2016/09/23/opinion/campaign-stops/donald-trumps-real-message-on-race.html"
data-title="Donald Trump’s Real Message on Race"
data-author="By ANDREW ROSENTHAL"
data-media="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2016/09/23/opinion/23rosenthalWeb/23rosenthalWeb-jumbo.jpg"
data-description="He claims his “movement” is for “everybody,” but his supporters know what he’s really saying."
	data-publish-date="September 22, 2016"
>
<a class="visually-hidden skip-to-text-link" href="#story-continues-1">Continue reading the main story</a>
<span class="sharetools-label visually-hidden">Share This Page</span>
<div class="ad sharetools-inline-article-ad hidden nocontent robots-nocontent">
<a class="visually-hidden skip-to-text-link" href="#story-continues-1">Continue reading the main story</a>
</div>
</div><!-- close shareTools -->
                                                    <button class="button comments-button  theme-speech-bubble" data-skip-to-para-id="">
</button>
                                            </div>
                            </div><!-- close story-meta-footer -->
        </div><!-- close story-meta -->
    </header>

    <script type="text/javascript">
        if (
            window.magnum
            && window.magnum.getFlags().indexOf('headlineBalancer') > 0
            && window.magnum.headlineBalancer
            && window.magnum.headlineBalancer.initialize
            && window.magnum.headlineBalancer.shouldRun()
        ) {
            window.magnum.headlineBalancer.initialize();
        }
    </script>

        
    <div class="story-body-supplemental">
    <div class="story-body story-body-1">
        <figure id="media-100000004665268" class="media photo lede layout-large-horizontal" data-media-action="modal" itemprop="associatedMedia" itemscope itemid="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2016/09/23/opinion/23rosenthalWeb/23rosenthalWeb-master768.jpg" itemtype="http://schema.org/ImageObject" aria-label="media" role="group">
    <span class="visually-hidden">Photo</span>
    <div class="image">
            <img src="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2016/09/23/opinion/23rosenthalWeb/23rosenthalWeb-master768.jpg" alt="" class="media-viewer-candidate" data-mediaviewer-src="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2016/09/23/opinion/23rosenthalWeb/23rosenthalWeb-superJumbo.jpg" data-mediaviewer-caption="Donald Trump campaigning in Florida on Monday." data-mediaviewer-credit="Eric Thayer for The New York Times"  itemprop="url" itemid="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2016/09/23/opinion/23rosenthalWeb/23rosenthalWeb-master768.jpg"/>
            <meta itemprop="height" content="512" />
            <meta itemprop="width" content="768" />
    </div>
        <figcaption class="caption" itemprop="caption description">
                <span class="caption-text">Donald Trump campaigning in Florida on Monday.</span>
                        <span class="credit" itemprop="copyrightHolder">
            <span class="visually-hidden">Credit</span>
            Eric Thayer for The New York Times        </span>
            </figcaption>
    </figure>
<p class="story-body-text story-content" data-para-count="102" data-total-count="102">The more Donald Trump presses his supposed effort to appeal to black voters, the more bizarre it gets.</p><p class="story-body-text story-content" data-para-count="209" data-total-count="311">Just this week, the Republican nominee for president said the answer to inner-city violence was to revive New York’s stop-and-frisk program, abandoned after federal courts ruled that the results were racist.</p><p class="story-body-text story-content" data-para-count="316" data-total-count="627">He <a href="http://talkingpointsmemo.com/news/trump-i-reversed-birther-stance-to-get-on-with-campaign">suggested</a> that his decision to recant his insidious “birther” claims against President Obama was an insincere attempt to change the subject. He <a href="https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/the-fix/wp/2016/09/22/donald-trumps-puzzling-appeal-to-black-voters-on-sean-hannitys-show-annotated/#annotations:10480465">declared</a> that his “movement” already embraces “everybody.” And one of his county campaign chairs announced that there was no racism before Obama was elected.</p><p class="story-body-text story-content" data-para-count="72" data-total-count="699">Not convinced that this is going to make black Americans vote for Trump?</p><p class="story-body-text story-content" data-para-count="180" data-total-count="879">That’s probably because Trump isn’t actually speaking to minority voters. He is offering excuses for white Americans who might otherwise hesitate to support a racist candidate.</p><p class="story-body-text story-content" data-para-count="239" data-total-count="1118">In 1980, as the political journalist Adam Clymer <a href="http://www.politico.com/story/2012/07/who-was-romney-really-talking-to-078461">pointed out</a>, Ronald Reagan pivoted from denouncing “welfare queens” to appearing before the National Urban League. He also persuaded a couple of prominent black ministers to endorse him.</p><div id="story-ad-1" class="story-ad ad ad-placeholder nocontent robots-nocontent">
    <div class="accessibility-ad-header visually-hidden">
    <p>Advertisement</p>
</div>
<a class="visually-hidden skip-to-text-link" href="#story-continues-1">Continue reading the main story</a>
</div>
<p class="story-body-text story-content" data-para-count="333" data-total-count="1451" id="story-continues-1">But African-Americans were not fooled. Reagan got little support from black voters, and Republican candidates who followed him did as badly or worse. Trump’s support among African-Americans is in the single digits. At his <a href="http://www.slate.com/blogs/the_slatest/2016/07/19/there_are_only_18_black_delegates_at_the_gop_convention_according_to_the.html">convention in Cleveland</a>, there were 18 African-American delegates, the smallest share in more than a century.</p><p class="story-body-text story-content" data-para-count="269" data-total-count="1720">Unlike Reagan, Trump skipped the Urban League meeting in August, but he did appear at a “town hall” meeting on Wednesday devoted to “<a href="http://thehill.com/blogs/blog-briefing-room/news/296699-trump-to-do-town-hall-at-black-church-with-hannity">core issues</a> and concerns surrounding African-Americans,” where Sean Hannity of Fox News obligingly served up softball questions.</p><p class="story-body-text story-content" data-para-count="228" data-total-count="1948">Not even Hannity, who seems to have joined the Trump campaign full time, could make Trump sound credible on race. At one point, he asked Trump how, specifically, his economic policies would help African-Americans. Trump replied:</p><blockquote class="story-quote story-content" data-para-count="458" data-total-count="2406"><p>We need jobs. Desperately need jobs. Now, obviously we need the schools, we need the education, we need all sorts of things, and especially the inner cities. The inner cities are — can you say never? But certainly one of the worst stages ever in the history of the inner city. It’s so unsafe, where you walk down the street and you get shot, or your child gets shot. So we’re going to really fix the inner cities, we’re going to spend a lot of time.</p></blockquote><p class="story-body-text story-content" data-para-count="201" data-total-count="2607">Trump then blamed Democratic mayors and Obama for a rising crime rate that made Chicago “worse than Afghanistan.” (It will shock you to learn that Chicago is a lot less dangerous than Afghanistan.)</p><p class="story-body-text story-content" data-para-count="200" data-total-count="2807">The answer? Stop-and-frisk. Trump said former New York Mayor Rudy Giuliani did a “great job” by giving the police the authority to stop people at random on the streets and search them for weapons.</p><p class="story-body-text story-content" data-para-count="305" data-total-count="3112">The crime rate in New York dropped in the ’90s, as it did around the country, but not because of stop-and-frisk. Of <a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2016/06/23/opinion/policing-the-police-on-stop-and-frisk.html?_r=0">nearly 4.5 million stops</a> conducted under the policy, only 6 percent resulted in arrests and 6 percent in summonses. In about 83 percent of cases, the person stopped was black or Hispanic.</p><p class="story-body-text story-content" data-para-count="117" data-total-count="3229">The trial judge declared stop-and-frisk unconstitutional, and it was ultimately ended. Trump thinks that’s a shame.</p><p class="story-body-text story-content" data-para-count="264" data-total-count="3493">So far, there’s no sign that his pitch is resonating with actual black voters. But the real message is getting through to his supporters, like Kathy Miller, chairman of the Trump campaign in Mahoning County, Ohio, which includes the rust-belt city of Youngstown.</p><p class="story-body-text story-content" data-para-count="109" data-total-count="3602">“I don’t think there was any racism until Obama got elected,” Miller told a reporter from The Guardian.</p><div class="newsletter-signup" id="newsletter-promo" data-newsletter-productCode="TY"  data-newsletter-productTitle="Opinion Today">
    <div class="single-newsletter-promo" data-newsletter-productCode="TY">
        <h2 class="headline">Sign Up for the Opinion Today Newsletter</h2>        <p class="summary">Every weekday, get thought-provoking commentary from Op-Ed columnists, the Times editorial board and contributing writers from around the world.</p>    </div>
